WEBVTT

00:23.284 --> 00:25.808
[traffic din]

00:27.505 --> 00:29.638
[Alex]
When I was very young,

00:29.812 --> 00:32.249
Sometimes I'’d lay
in bed at night...

00:32.423 --> 00:35.209
and imagined that my family
turned into monsters

00:35.383 --> 00:37.863
when I fell asleep.

00:38.038 --> 00:39.996
Listening to the hum
of urban traffic

00:40.170 --> 00:41.867
outside my window,

00:42.042 --> 00:44.435
I could picture them
having wild revelries,

00:44.609 --> 00:48.135
sure to explode
my 8-year-old mind.

00:48.309 --> 00:50.615
And, of course, there was
a thoroughly logical belief

00:50.789 --> 00:53.618
that they were fattening me up
just to eat me.

00:53.792 --> 00:57.144
Even now,
at the ripe old age of 16,

00:57.318 --> 00:59.798
I still catch myself
asking the same old question.

01:01.365 --> 01:02.714
Who are you people?

01:09.330 --> 01:12.289
And lately,
rather than recede,

01:12.463 --> 01:14.639
that question
only gets louder.

01:14.813 --> 01:16.685
Consider my father.

01:16.859 --> 01:19.209
He's a shark litigator,
who simultaneously craves

01:19.383 --> 01:21.820
both the nobility of laboring
for the disenfranchised

01:21.994 --> 01:24.432
and the splatter of blood
from those who dare oppose him.

01:25.694 --> 01:27.217
Perhaps that's why

01:27.391 --> 01:28.784
his emotional
communication switch

01:28.958 --> 01:30.090
is permanently stuck
on "yell."

01:30.264 --> 01:31.569
