you went to Portland?

35:49.669 --> 35:50.713
How old were you?

35:51.323 --> 35:53.629
I was about 20,
21, I guess.

35:53.803 --> 35:54.935
So, let me
get this straight.

35:55.109 --> 35:56.676
Your dead mom's cousin

35:56.850 --> 35:59.069
just, like,
gave you this place?

35:59.244 --> 36:00.549
You know,
you ask a lot of questions.

36:00.723 --> 36:02.290
Oh, and Gayle,
what is up with her?

36:02.464 --> 36:03.944
That wasn'’t a request
for more.

36:04.118 --> 36:05.424
I think it's really weird
that you, like,

36:05.598 --> 36:07.034
-don't date at all.
-[Karl sighs]

36:07.513 --> 36:08.557
What's up with that?

36:09.558 --> 36:10.603
Let me ask you something.

36:11.604 --> 36:13.475
You've been here,
what, four days?

36:14.476 --> 36:16.043
Your parents okay
with you missing school?

36:17.349 --> 36:19.481
I'm on break.
You can call and ask.

36:19.655 --> 36:20.787
Yeah.

36:20.961 --> 36:22.223
That's what made you decide

36:22.397 --> 36:23.355
now is the time
to take this trip?

36:24.704 --> 36:27.620
Nothing you'd rather
keep to yourself?

36:30.144 --> 36:31.406
I'm going to
make you a deal.

36:31.972 --> 36:33.452
You hold off
on asking me questions

36:33.626 --> 36:34.931
I'm not comfortable
answering just yet,

36:35.105 --> 36:36.933
and I'll do the same,
okay?

36:37.891 --> 36:39.675
-Cool.
-Cool.

36:47.770 --> 36:49.468
It's cool you know
how these things work.

36:51.992 --> 36:53.733
My parents
are completely useless.

36:54.690 --> 36:56.475
They can't even
program a smart TV.

36:56.649 --> 36:57.998
They went to college, right?

36:58.999 --> 37:00.218
Got good jobs?

37:00.696 --> 37:02.350
They're a product
of their social class.

37:03.395 --> 37:05.266
There's nothing noble
about being ignorant.

37:05.832 --> 37:09.096
Not knowing shit about shit
is nothing to celebrate.

37:09.966 --> 37:11.054
Got me?

37:11.533 --> 37:13.579
[Reggie]
So, who do we have here?

37:13.753 --> 37:15.885
[tense music plays]

37:16.059 --> 37:18.148
Spotted your new guest
last Sunday.

37:22.718 --> 37:23.937
You gonna introduce us?

37:26.766 --> 37:28.420
Alex,
this is Sheriff Stratford.

37:29.116 --> 37:30.552
Hi.

37:31.727 --> 37:33.033
[Karl] May I help you
with something?

37:34.295 --> 37:37.342
Just wanted to stop by,
catch up.

37:39.126 --> 37:40.562
You see me
every week at church.

37:40.736 --> 37:41.824
[Reggie] I do.

37:43.217 --> 37:45.828
Saw you in church
a few years back as well.

37:46.002 --> 37:47.395
You know
how that worked out.

37:53.662 --> 37:54.750
Well.

37:55.795 --> 37:56.839
All right.

37:59.712 --> 38:01.714
Brandon says hi,
by the way.

38:07.546 --> 38:09.025
[door clicks open]

38:09.199 --> 38:12.072
[Sarah] I saw Gayle
at school today.

38:12.942 --> 38:14.117
She asked about you.

38:16.903 --> 38:18.252
Is that a corner piece?

38:18.426 --> 38:19.862
-Yes.
-Okay.

38:21.168 --> 38:22.256
Oh, yes.

38:23.301 --> 38:24.432
Look at that.

38:24.606 --> 38:28.741
[mellow piano melody plays]

39:00.468 --> 39:01.730
What are you doing?

39:05.299 --> 39:06.431
Did you do that?

39:09.782 --> 39:10.696
Yeah.

39:10.870 --> 39:15.614
♪

39:25.885 --> 39:27.800
[Alex] Judith thinks it's,
like, a massive waste of time.

39:27.974 --> 39:29.584
[Karl] No, you'’re good.

39:30.629 --> 39:31.847
Hm, not really.

39:33.414 --> 39:34.589
Better than I ever was.

39:37.157 --> 39:39.246
Hey, this is my mom, right?

39:43.772 --> 39:44.947
Your mom...

39:46.253 --> 39:47.689
discovered me.

39:49.778 --> 39:51.084
-What?
-[Karl] Yeah.

39:51.258 --> 39:53.303
-My mom?
-Yeah.

39:57.743 --> 40:00.180
I went to Portland
to be an artist.

40:03.618 --> 40:06.839
Liked the idea of being
around bookstores and museums.

40:09.929 --> 40:12.410
And anyways, I was bussing
at a café down on Alberta.

40:13.541 --> 40:15.500
The owner must have felt
sorry for me, I think,

40:15.674 --> 40:17.719
because he put
one of my pictures on the wall.

40:19.373 --> 40:20.722
"Featured Local Artist"

40:20.896 --> 40:26.032
with this stupid
$200 price tag.

40:26.989 --> 40:28.077
[Karl scoffs]

40:29.818 --> 40:31.559
Your mom
came in sometimes.

40:33.169 --> 40:35.171
She used to like to write
in her notebook.

40:37.173 --> 40:39.828
One day,
I was clearing her table,

40:40.002 --> 40:42.309
and she said
that she liked it,

40:42.483 --> 40:44.442
and I said
that I drew it.

40:45.660 --> 40:46.966
And, uh...

40:48.097 --> 40:51.971
she was almost giddy.

40:53.755 --> 40:56.497
She knew a lot of people
in a lot of different places

40:56.671 --> 40:58.586
and said she'd help me
organize a show.

40:59.587 --> 41:01.328
She was the only one
to give a damn.

41:02.111 --> 41:03.678
So that's how it started...

41:05.245 --> 41:06.420
with you two?

41:09.118 --> 41:11.469
Before I met her, she said
she had been a party girl.

41:13.035 --> 41:15.473
And then she married
this big shot lawyer

41:15.647 --> 41:17.170
and became
something different.

41:19.999 --> 41:21.174
They were trying
to have a baby,

41:21.348 --> 41:22.392
and it wasn't working.

41:23.393 --> 41:25.744
So I think
she saw my drawings

41:25.918 --> 41:28.181
and figured
it'd be something to do.

41:31.227 --> 41:32.272
[Alex] So, what happened?

41:33.403 --> 41:35.318
Did she put on
your art show?

41:35.493 --> 41:36.711
-My mom?
-[Karl] No.

41:36.885 --> 41:39.671
No, we--
we had some postcards

41:39.845 --> 41:41.977
printed up,
and that's about it.

41:44.023 --> 41:45.111
[Alex] How come?

41:47.156 --> 41:48.201
How come?

41:50.725 --> 41:51.900
Because...

41:53.554 --> 41:56.122
I wasn't always
such a good guy and...

41:58.298 --> 41:59.821
your mom found that out.

42:04.478 --> 42:06.393
[Alex] I saw the letter
that you wrote her.

42:08.308 --> 42:11.267
Having an affair isn't,
like, awesome, but, uh--

42:13.052 --> 42:14.488
You got me out of it, right?

42:18.448 --> 42:19.580
Yeah, I guess we did.

42:23.889 --> 42:25.412
Was there something else
that was, like...

42:26.326 --> 42:27.762
bad about you?

42:28.328 --> 42:29.721
I have an early morning.

42:29.895 --> 42:31.723
Uh, can I keep that?

42:35.770 --> 42:36.728
Yeah.

42:36.902 --> 42:41.820
♪

42:55.268 --> 42:56.617
[Alex] Hey, hey, hey.

42:57.183 --> 42:58.532
-Good morning.
-Morning.

42:59.359 --> 43:00.708
So, uh, where's Karl?

43:01.361 --> 43:02.971
Meeting.

43:03.145 --> 43:05.757
So, it'’s a "I accept
Jesus as my savior

43:05.931 --> 43:07.715
so I won't get bombed"
type thing?

43:08.803 --> 43:10.370
Not to, like,
offend Jesus or anything.

43:10.544 --> 43:12.764
No, Jesus has heard worse.

43:14.026 --> 43:15.288
Do you really think
he believes in it?

43:16.855 --> 43:18.639
Because
you act like he does

43:18.813 --> 43:20.249
and he acts
like he does, but...

43:21.468 --> 43:23.557
Kind of seems like
he just wants to believe it.

43:29.302 --> 43:30.912
I'm truly glad
you're here.

43:32.000 --> 43:33.132
I think
it's good for him.

43:34.133 --> 43:35.743
And I don't care
what you think of my faith...

43:37.397 --> 43:38.790
but maybe you want to think

43:38.964 --> 43:41.096
that Karl doesn't really
believe either,

43:41.270 --> 43:43.446
and that's something
the two of you could share.

43:45.144 --> 43:47.973
But those beliefs
saved him.

43:53.935 --> 43:55.633
Well, I'm not
the only one who thinks that.

43:56.503 --> 43:57.896
Sheriff called
him out on it, too.

43:59.071 --> 44:00.115
You met the sheriff?

44:01.334 --> 44:04.467
Did Karl, like, steal
his prom date or something?

44:05.381 --> 44:07.296
No.
I'll be back tonight.

44:10.517 --> 44:12.650
Please tell Karl
that dinner is at 7:00.

44:15.740 --> 44:21.789
[melancholy piano instrumental]

44:27.273 --> 44:28.448
Okay.

44:32.757 --> 44:33.845
Hi.

44:34.410 --> 44:36.717
-Can I help you?
-What's your problem with Karl?

44:37.544 --> 44:40.068
-You're his kid, right?
-[Alex] Mm.

44:40.242 --> 44:41.287
You should be a detective.

44:41.809 --> 44:43.028
[Reggie chuckles]

44:49.382 --> 44:51.210
I hate uncomfortable silences.

44:51.993 --> 44:53.212
I'm fine with them.

44:54.909 --> 44:56.737
-Your mom know you're here?
-Of course.

45:01.089 --> 45:02.134
Have a seat.

45:07.705 --> 45:08.967
[Alex] So what's your issue?

45:10.490 --> 45:13.275
We used to bust your old man
pretty routinely.

45:13.449 --> 45:15.016
Drunk and disorderly.

45:15.190 --> 45:17.453
Disturbing the peace,
that sort of thing.

45:18.585 --> 45:20.369
Last time
he fell off the wagon,

45:20.543 --> 45:22.981
he put his fist
through a storefront window.

45:23.764 --> 45:26.549
Were you, like, emotionally
invested in that window?

45:29.683 --> 45:31.206
About a dozen years ago...

45:32.468 --> 45:33.556
your dad got loaded.

45:34.035 --> 45:36.037
Beat the crap
out of a 19-year-old

45:36.211 --> 45:39.345
varsity linebacker named
Brandon in a bar fight.

45:41.564 --> 45:43.741
Kid lost his hearing
in his left ear.

45:44.872 --> 45:46.569
Arm was in a cast
for weeks.

45:46.744 --> 45:48.920
Supposed to go to the army.
They wouldn't take him.

45:49.094 --> 45:50.530
You're weirdly concerned

45:50.704 --> 45:51.749
with the well-being of your
residents.

45:52.227 --> 45:53.663
Especially
when they're my son.

45:57.276 --> 45:59.408
After that,
Karl got put away.

45:59.582 --> 46:02.020
He had some priors,
served five.

46:06.546 --> 46:08.200
Well, he goes
to meetings now.

46:11.986 --> 46:14.554
I've seen
all kinds of drunks.

46:16.121 --> 46:17.470
Kind that are good
for a laugh,

46:17.644 --> 46:19.124
tell you how much
they love you.

46:20.473 --> 46:22.954
But Karl Hendrix
gets violent.

46:24.042 --> 46:27.088
He is a drunk,
dangerous criminal.

46:28.046 --> 46:29.830
And a drunk,
dangerous criminal

46:30.004 --> 46:33.007
doesn't really change because
he goes to an AA meeting.

46:33.660 --> 46:36.271
Or says he found God
or what have you.

46:38.621 --> 46:41.407
I know it's not an excuse
or anything,

46:41.581 --> 46:42.930
but he had
a really hard life.

46:43.888 --> 46:45.672
His dad sounds
like a total asshole.

46:45.846 --> 46:47.587
Yeah, I know Beau Hendrix.

46:48.327 --> 46:50.198
-You knew him?
-No, I know him.

46:51.243 --> 46:52.418
Well, he's dead, right?

46:54.028 --> 46:56.422
He lives two towns over
in Bryantville.

46:57.727 --> 46:59.294
Karl told you he was dead?

47:02.297 --> 47:03.516
Do you have the address?

47:04.909 --> 47:09.827
[suspenseful music plays]

47:17.747 --> 47:19.880
[thunder cracking]

47:44.687 --> 47:45.688
[knocking on door]

47:45.863 --> 47:47.995
[thunder rolling]

47:56.569 --> 47:57.875
Who are you?

47:58.049 --> 48:00.225
I'm Alex.
Your granddaughter.

48:03.619 --> 48:05.534
[Beau snickering]

48:08.537 --> 48:09.843
Maybe-- maybe
this is a bad time.

48:10.017 --> 48:11.192
[Beau] No.

48:11.932 --> 48:12.977
It'’s a fine time.

48:15.762 --> 48:17.677
Let's sit on my porch.

48:19.461 --> 48:20.854
Granddaughter Alex.

48:21.724 --> 48:26.468
[somber tone plays]

48:27.165 --> 48:28.209
So.

48:29.819 --> 48:32.431
I haven't seen Karl
in going on, what?

48:34.085 --> 48:35.173
Ten years?

48:37.610 --> 48:38.698
Didn't know about you.

48:40.874 --> 48:42.920
I'm kind of like
a-- a long story.

48:45.661 --> 48:46.706
Well, I got time.

48:51.363 --> 48:52.407
Hey, Reg.

48:53.017 --> 48:54.061
Look who's here.

48:56.672 --> 48:58.413
Have you seen Alex?

48:58.587 --> 49:00.720
Sarah mentioned you talked
and she hasn't been home.

49:00.894 --> 49:02.200
-So--
-You all right there?

49:05.159 --> 49:06.769
Tried her
on her cell phone?

49:08.946 --> 49:10.077
I don'’t have the number.

49:10.643 --> 49:12.471
[scoffs] Father of the year.

49:12.645 --> 49:13.907
[Karl] Please.

49:14.473 --> 49:16.040
I just need to know
where she went, that's all.

49:16.954 --> 49:18.738
I'm not certain
where she went.

49:19.695 --> 49:22.046
I can tell you
there's a lot she doesn't know.

49:23.308 --> 49:26.093
Thought her grandfather
was dead, for one thing.

49:26.267 --> 49:30.271
[suspenseful music plays]

49:44.764 --> 49:46.766
So it, like, turns out
that we sort of have the same,

49:46.940 --> 49:48.594
like, drawing style.

49:49.682 --> 49:51.640
Like, I don't know
if-- if I really believe

49:51.814 --> 49:54.556
in the nature
over nurture argument,

49:54.730 --> 49:56.732
but I really do think that,
like, there might be,

49:56.906 --> 49:59.779
like, some sort of compelling
argument for the fact that,

49:59.953 --> 50:03.783
like, genes affect
artistic stylings, you know?

50:05.176 --> 50:06.438
You know, um...

50:07.700 --> 50:09.136
Karl and Sarah are probably
wondering where I am.

50:09.310 --> 50:10.355
Who Sarah?

50:11.834 --> 50:14.011
Karl'’s cousin, Sarah Kelly.

50:15.316 --> 50:17.101
His mom's cousin,
Sarah Kelly?

50:18.058 --> 50:19.364
-The church lady?
-Yeah.

50:20.147 --> 50:22.019
Uh, he runs her shop
and he's actually, like,

50:22.193 --> 50:23.629
a really good mechanic.

50:25.196 --> 50:26.980
[Beau chuckling]
How about that?

50:27.154 --> 50:29.156
Oh, he'’s-- he's here.

50:30.331 --> 50:31.376
Alex.

50:33.378 --> 50:34.466
Karl.

50:36.729 --> 50:37.860
Come here.

50:40.994 --> 50:42.256
[Beau groans]

50:43.301 --> 50:44.389
So.

50:45.172 --> 50:46.434
Where you been
hiding yourself?

50:47.653 --> 50:48.741
Keep busy.

50:49.350 --> 50:50.351
[Beau chuckles]

50:50.917 --> 50:52.266
This is great.

50:52.440 --> 50:54.703
Sit down, have a beer.

50:55.269 --> 50:56.662
No, we can't stay long.

50:57.228 --> 50:58.620
What are you talking about?

50:58.794 --> 50:59.969
You just got here.

51:00.144 --> 51:02.276
Sit down, have a beer.

51:04.235 --> 51:05.366
[Beau grunts]

51:11.894 --> 51:15.115
Alex here was telling me
you two draw alike.

51:16.029 --> 51:17.335
More artists!

51:18.466 --> 51:19.598
That's what we need.

51:21.513 --> 51:23.950
Did he tell you I worked
40 years at the plant?

51:25.169 --> 51:27.780
Got to know your place, right?

51:32.132 --> 51:33.351
You're not thirsty?

51:35.701 --> 51:36.919
No, I'm all right.

51:38.356 --> 51:39.444
Oh.

51:40.271 --> 51:43.056
Oh. I get it.

51:43.839 --> 51:45.319
You and the bottle.

51:46.059 --> 51:47.365
It never led anywhere good.

51:47.539 --> 51:48.975
You know what,
it's getting late--

51:49.149 --> 51:50.716
Maybe if you would have
sobered up sooner

51:50.890 --> 51:52.283
or you wouldn't have put
that kid in the hospital.

51:53.806 --> 51:57.940
I mean, of all the asses
in the world you gotta kick...

51:59.028 --> 52:00.508
that's the one you choose?

52:00.682 --> 52:03.946
-We should get going.
-Why that kid, Karl?

52:05.165 --> 52:06.732
I really want to know.

52:10.214 --> 52:11.780
[Karl] I didn't like the way
he was touching

52:11.954 --> 52:14.000
that girl at the bar, Dad,
I told you that already.

52:14.392 --> 52:15.915
[Beau] Well, that's an answer.

52:17.003 --> 52:18.657
-That's a fucking--
-You're an asshole.

52:20.876 --> 52:22.487
-What was that, honey?
-Alex, stop--

52:22.661 --> 52:23.792
No, you're a bully
and you don't like your son

52:23.966 --> 52:25.098
because he's better than you.

52:25.620 --> 52:28.057
Who the fuck
do you think you are?

52:29.798 --> 52:31.539
Huh? Huh? What you got? Huh?

52:31.713 --> 52:32.845
[Alex] Stop!

52:41.810 --> 52:43.116
Visit's over.

52:44.857 --> 52:45.988
Get out of here.

52:46.554 --> 52:49.731
-I'm so sorry.
-The hell were you thinking?

52:49.905 --> 52:51.429
You-- you told me he was dead.

52:51.603 --> 52:53.082
It ever occur to you
I had a reason?

52:54.475 --> 52:56.173
Shit. Fuck. I'm sorry.

52:56.347 --> 52:57.826
I-- I suck, I suck, I suck.

52:58.000 --> 52:59.176
Get in the car.

52:59.698 --> 53:02.179
-Get in the car.
-You can yell at me some more.

53:07.009 --> 53:08.141
You're going home tomorrow.

53:13.233 --> 53:15.148
[footsteps approaching]

53:17.585 --> 53:18.630
Hi.

53:18.804 --> 53:20.371
Dinner will be ready in five...

53:22.460 --> 53:23.591
minutes.

53:27.029 --> 53:30.163
[melancholic
piano instrumental]

54:02.935 --> 54:04.197
[Arthur] You stalker.

54:05.677 --> 54:09.376
So, shockingly,
I have fucked everything up.

54:09.855 --> 54:12.553
Well, at least you and your dad
were getting along well.

54:13.293 --> 54:14.468
[Alex scoffs]

54:14.642 --> 54:15.904
Yeah,
if by getting along well

54:16.078 --> 54:17.950
you mean
yelling at me a lot.

54:18.820 --> 54:20.213
Which I guess is, like,

54:20.387 --> 54:21.388
par for the course
of parents, right?

54:23.303 --> 54:25.218
He was probably scared
something had happened to you.

54:26.524 --> 54:28.003
He screamed
because he gives a shit.

54:30.745 --> 54:32.225
So how long
have you known you were gay?

54:33.792 --> 54:37.665
Okay, you're from a major
metropolitan city,

54:37.839 --> 54:39.276
so you've seen probably

54:39.450 --> 54:41.713
every weird form
of pansexuality out there.

54:41.887 --> 54:43.758
I mean, you have
probably fucked girls.

54:43.932 --> 54:46.108
Oh, yeah.
My life is just a big orgy.

54:46.283 --> 54:47.588
Yeah, I'm sure it is.

54:48.110 --> 54:49.721
-You didn't answer my question.
-You didn't answer mine.

54:50.635 --> 54:51.766
Have you hooked up
with a girl?

54:53.507 --> 54:54.813
Have you?

54:55.683 --> 54:56.945
I'm a godless fag, remember?

54:57.990 --> 54:59.034
[Alex] Really?

55:05.432 --> 55:06.477
-Alex--
-It's okay.

55:11.438 --> 55:13.222
Okay, I gotta go. [chuckles]

55:16.530 --> 55:17.879
Okay.

55:18.053 --> 55:22.623
[quiet, subtle piano
instrumental]

55:33.373 --> 55:35.941
You disappeared again.
Are you kidding me?

55:36.420 --> 55:37.682
Apparently not.

55:38.160 --> 55:40.206
Whoa, whoa, whoa.
Where the hell did you go?

55:40.380 --> 55:42.643
-I was with Arthur.
-The gay kid?

55:42.817 --> 55:44.819
-Pretty sure he's not gay.
-How the hell do you know that?

55:44.993 --> 55:46.473
-How is that your business?
-You know, as long as

55:46.647 --> 55:47.692
you're in this house,
you do exactly--

55:47.866 --> 55:48.910
Oh, until tomorrow?

55:50.042 --> 55:51.130
Go to your room.

55:51.826 --> 55:53.828
-Go to your room.
-Oh, go to my room?

55:54.002 --> 55:56.353
That's so original, "Dad."

55:57.702 --> 55:58.746
[door shuts close]

