1:32:38.378 --> 1:32:39.423
He's still my dad.

1:32:41.512 --> 1:32:42.731
And maybe it's a test.

1:32:44.080 --> 1:32:45.429
Maybe it's God's test.

1:32:47.257 --> 1:32:48.519
You don't believe in that.

1:32:49.607 --> 1:32:50.826
You don't care
what I believe.

1:32:53.480 --> 1:32:54.917
All that matters
is whether you do.

1:32:56.701 --> 1:32:57.746
Right.

1:32:59.661 --> 1:33:01.924
[sniffles] Well,

1:33:02.098 --> 1:33:05.231
-no more cutting school, okay?
-Yes, ma'am.

1:33:06.842 --> 1:33:08.234
Come here.

1:33:11.890 --> 1:33:12.978
-Bye.
-Bye.

1:33:13.979 --> 1:33:17.940
[upbeat music playing]

1:33:27.863 --> 1:33:28.994
[Alex] "Hey, Arthur.

1:33:30.996 --> 1:33:32.781
Sorry it's taken me
so long to write.

1:33:34.783 --> 1:33:37.612
I wish I could say
I had a good excuse.

1:33:37.786 --> 1:33:41.354
Because I was off having
pansexual underground orgies

1:33:41.528 --> 1:33:44.575
or going to only
the hottest club openings,

1:33:44.749 --> 1:33:46.359
but sadly..."

1:33:46.533 --> 1:33:48.623
-Well, look who's here.
-Yeah, I'm finally back.

1:33:48.797 --> 1:33:50.973
[Alex] "...I think I'm still
trying to process stuff."

1:33:51.147 --> 1:33:53.279
Thank you [indistinct].

1:33:53.453 --> 1:33:55.020
[Alex] "At least
that's what the shrink

1:33:55.194 --> 1:33:56.761
my parents
are making me see says..."

1:33:56.935 --> 1:33:58.197
Alex? Hi.

1:33:58.371 --> 1:33:59.982
Come on back.

1:34:00.156 --> 1:34:01.070
[Alex] "...keeps me out
of boarding school."

1:34:01.244 --> 1:34:02.201
How are you?

1:34:02.375 --> 1:34:04.247
-Good.
-Good.

1:34:04.421 --> 1:34:06.118
[Alex] "Which is great
because I love my school..."

1:34:06.292 --> 1:34:08.338
Next up, The Age of Innocence
by Edith Wharton.

1:34:08.512 --> 1:34:09.600
[Alex] "...so much."

1:34:10.557 --> 1:34:12.255
[classmate scoffs]
Jailbait.

1:34:12.429 --> 1:34:14.344
[Mrs. Rumble] So, who got
through the first chapter?

1:34:17.129 --> 1:34:18.870
Okay, I do not snore!

1:34:19.044 --> 1:34:21.264
[overlapping chatter]

1:34:21.438 --> 1:34:23.309
You're just telling me
that I snore now?

1:34:23.483 --> 1:34:24.789
No, no, no, no,

1:34:24.963 --> 1:34:26.748
-it's a little tiny noise.
-Okay.

1:34:26.922 --> 1:34:29.011
[Alex] "My parents
are also seeing a therapist.

1:34:29.185 --> 1:34:31.013
This is good because they are
basically

1:34:31.187 --> 1:34:32.754
the reason
therapy was invented."

1:34:32.928 --> 1:34:34.756
I mean, you can always
just sleep on the couch.

1:34:36.932 --> 1:34:38.760
-Okay.
-[Alex] Problem solved.

1:34:38.934 --> 1:34:40.631
"As for how I'm doing,

1:34:40.805 --> 1:34:41.937
I'm okay.

1:34:42.111 --> 1:34:43.852
Everything feels different,

1:34:44.026 --> 1:34:46.768
but everything also
sort of feels exactly the same.

1:34:46.942 --> 1:34:48.465
When I first got back,
I sort of thought

1:34:48.639 --> 1:34:50.641
my room would be
a different color or something."

1:34:50.989 --> 1:34:54.340
Circumcised, uncircumcised,
very different things.

1:34:54.514 --> 1:34:56.603
[Alex] "I thought
I should cut my hair

1:34:56.778 --> 1:34:58.693
or pierce my nose or get some
dumb Chinese character tattoo

1:34:58.867 --> 1:35:01.217
that means strength
or something.

1:35:01.391 --> 1:35:04.089
Just to be like, 'Hello, world.
I'm different now.'

1:35:05.264 --> 1:35:07.963
And then I thought, 'Wow.

1:35:08.137 --> 1:35:09.704
How boldly cliché.'

1:35:12.663 --> 1:35:15.535
In general,
I'm trying to suck less."

1:35:15.710 --> 1:35:20.715
♪

1:35:24.240 --> 1:35:26.155
"I haven't talked to Karl.

1:35:30.072 --> 1:35:31.856
Right now,
I'm smoking a cigarette,

1:35:32.030 --> 1:35:33.423
poorly,

1:35:33.597 --> 1:35:34.685
just for you.

1:35:36.208 --> 1:35:38.036
Come visit.

1:35:38.210 --> 1:35:39.429
If anyone asks
how we knew each other,

1:35:39.603 --> 1:35:40.996
I guess I can just lie.

1:35:42.998 --> 1:35:46.044
I mean,
better get used to that, right?

1:35:48.046 --> 1:35:50.309
Love, Alex."

1:35:51.397 --> 1:35:54.096
[coughing]

1:36:02.104 --> 1:36:03.453
Hey.

1:36:03.627 --> 1:36:05.455
Dad. Can you knock?

1:36:08.371 --> 1:36:09.415
It's him.

1:36:19.861 --> 1:36:20.905
I'll be right outside.

1:36:28.913 --> 1:36:30.610
Hello?

1:36:30.785 --> 1:36:32.917
[Karl] Hey there.

1:36:33.091 --> 1:36:35.180
I figured it'd be better
to be direct with your folks.

1:36:36.486 --> 1:36:38.488
-Mm-hmm.
-[Karl] How are you?

1:36:42.579 --> 1:36:44.886
-Okay.
-[Karl] Are you back at school?

1:36:47.149 --> 1:36:48.585
Yeah.

1:36:48.759 --> 1:36:49.804
[Karl]
Parents all right?

1:36:52.763 --> 1:36:54.809
-Mm-hmm.
-[Karl] Good.

1:36:56.158 --> 1:36:57.202
Good.

1:36:59.988 --> 1:37:02.164
Sorry it took so long
to call you, it's, uh,

1:37:02.338 --> 1:37:04.427
spent a couple more months
back in, uh...

1:37:06.995 --> 1:37:08.561
Reggie told them
to take it easy on me,

1:37:08.735 --> 1:37:09.780
if you can believe that.

1:37:12.391 --> 1:37:13.436
Okay.

1:37:16.569 --> 1:37:17.919
We had a good time here
tonight.

1:37:19.529 --> 1:37:21.226
Gayle from Sarah's work
came by and..

1:37:23.011 --> 1:37:26.318
I just-- I just slipped out
to call you.

1:37:27.232 --> 1:37:28.581
Sounds like
we're being rude.

1:37:31.933 --> 1:37:33.151
I needed
to tell you something.

1:37:36.241 --> 1:37:37.329
[Alex] Um...

1:37:39.592 --> 1:37:40.680
okay.

1:37:43.683 --> 1:37:44.946
That last night
you were here...

1:37:47.600 --> 1:37:50.516
when I was, uh,
I was drunk out of my mind...

1:37:52.954 --> 1:37:54.869
I was talking to Reggie
about Puritans.

1:37:57.872 --> 1:37:59.308
And how hard
it was for them

1:37:59.482 --> 1:38:00.483
not knowing
if they were damned.

1:38:02.528 --> 1:38:05.705
Well, the worst part
isn't not knowing.

1:38:09.100 --> 1:38:10.406
The worst part is knowing.

1:38:14.540 --> 1:38:16.238
That's how it was
until, uh...

1:38:18.893 --> 1:38:20.111
Until what?

1:38:24.289 --> 1:38:25.334
...'til you showed up.

1:38:29.686 --> 1:38:31.296
My mouth
is full of toothpaste.

1:38:35.648 --> 1:38:38.695
I know you have to go,
but, uh, we were--

1:38:38.869 --> 1:38:41.741
I was, uh,
I was thinking...

1:38:43.439 --> 1:38:45.615
that maybe
when the weather warms up and--

1:38:45.789 --> 1:38:48.183
and, you know, if it's okay
with your parents, that...

1:38:49.836 --> 1:38:50.925
well...

1:38:54.711 --> 1:38:55.930
maybe you could visit
some time.

1:38:56.104 --> 1:38:57.148
No.

1:39:01.500 --> 1:39:03.067
I mean, maybe.

1:39:07.898 --> 1:39:08.943
I don't know.

1:39:18.778 --> 1:39:20.084
[Karl] Alex?

1:39:25.742 --> 1:39:26.830
Alex?

1:39:28.484 --> 1:39:29.528
I'm here.

1:39:32.662 --> 1:39:33.750
Okay.

1:39:35.708 --> 1:39:37.101
Well, um...

1:39:39.060 --> 1:39:40.104
I'll let you go.

1:39:48.895 --> 1:39:52.899
[somber,
contemplative music playing]

1:40:52.046 --> 1:40:57.051
♪

1:41:57.111 --> 1:42:02.116
♪

1:43:18.714 --> 1:43:23.719
♪
